WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.200
How do we scale a high-ticket consultancy through DesignOps and automation?

00:04.200 --> 00:07.500
Welcome to the Holofante ecosystem.

00:07.500 --> 00:11.000
In the client app, the interface is state-driven.

00:11.000 --> 00:16.000
Here we see a project with confirmed payment and deliveries in progress.

00:16.000 --> 00:21.000
The engine behind it all is our Notion CRM and backend.

00:21.000 --> 00:26.000
When creating a test quote, the system begins the data orchestration.

00:26.000 --> 00:29.500
I fill in the email and the company size.

00:29.500 --> 00:36.000
This variable is critical: it automatically defines the price multiplier and contractual deadlines.

00:36.000 --> 00:41.000
By clicking send, we trigger an agentic orchestration via LangChain.

00:41.000 --> 00:48.000
The system takes control, generates a unique UUID, and starts scheduling the client's data.

00:48.000 --> 00:56.000
In seconds, the Node backend integration processes the data and fires a personalized transactional notification.

00:56.000 --> 01:02.000
The client receives an email with optimized UX, detailing the next steps.

01:02.000 --> 01:08.000
Contract via Clicksign E-signature and billing via Asaas Fintech.

01:08.000 --> 01:12.500
Upon clicking, they are taken to the dynamic quote page.

01:12.500 --> 01:21.000
Here, the URL uses the UUID to ensure privacy and prevent AI indexing.

01:21.000 --> 01:28.000
The values you see are calculated in real-time by backend formulas and protected by encryption.

01:28.000 --> 01:30.500
The sync is bidirectional.

01:30.500 --> 01:38.000
As soon as the client views the quote, the status in our CRM instantly changes to "Quote Viewed".

01:38.000 --> 01:47.000
Moving to the roadmap stage, when I finish the client manual in Notion and click send, the DesignOps magic happens.

01:47.000 --> 01:56.000
The system downloads the file, uploads it to a secure bucket, and triggers a real-time push notification.

01:56.000 --> 02:01.000
In the app, the stage status changes to "Pending Evaluation".

02:01.000 --> 02:07.500
The client doesn't access a generic link, but an authenticated route.

02:07.500 --> 02:16.000
Download links are temporary, expiring in 24 hours to protect the intellectual property of the delivery.

02:16.000 --> 02:18.500
The approval flow is rigorous.

02:18.500 --> 02:27.500
The client reviews and approves directly through the interface, which logs the timestamp and moves the project.

02:27.500 --> 02:29.200
Approval confirmed.

02:29.200 --> 02:33.500
The app unlocks the next stage, automating the final product delivery.

02:33.500 --> 02:37.500
In the CRM, the card moves automatically to "Approved".

02:37.500 --> 02:42.500
This is Product-Led Growth applied to Design as a Service.